|---------|---------|---------------|-------|
| Chrome | 66+ | Full | Recommended |
| Firefox | 60+ | Full | Full support |
| Safari | 14.1+ | Full | Full support |
| Edge | 79+ | Full | Full support |

## Performance Considerations

- **Memory Usage**: ~2-5MB for typical experiments
- **CPU Overhead**: <1% for normal scheduling operations
- **Task Latency**: <1ms for REALTIME priority tasks
- **Concurrent Tasks**: Supports up to 100 concurrent tasks

## License

MIT License - see LICENSE file for details.

## Contributing

This package is part of the Psycho-Forge project. See the main repository for contribution guidelines.

## Support

For scheduling-related issues, please include:
- Experiment structure and timeline hierarchy
- Task priorities and timing requirements
- Performance statistics from `getStats()`
- Browser version and platform information

