# @psyforge/forgescript

Domain-specific language and runtime for creating psychological experiments with TypeScript fluent API, comprehensive serialization, and precise timing integration.

## Features

- **Fluent TypeScript API**: Intuitive, type-safe experiment creation
- **Hierarchical Timelines**: Nested experiment structures with parent-child relationships
- **Comprehensive Stimuli**: Text, Image, Audio, Video stimuli with precise timing
- **Response Collection**: Keyboard, Mouse, Touch response collectors
- **Event-Driven Flow**: Conditional logic, loops, and data collection events
- **Serialization**: Complete JSON serialization with validation and migration
- **Runtime Execution**: Standalone runtime for experiment execution
- **Cross-Platform**: Works across desktop and mobile browsers
- **Timing Integration**: Frame-accurate timing with @psyforge/timing
- **Device Integration**: Unified device management with @psyforge/devices

## Installation

```bash
npm install @psyforge/forgescript @psyforge/timing @psyforge/devices @psyforge/scheduling
```

## Quick Start

Create a simple reaction time experiment:

```typescript
import { createExperiment, TextStimulus, KeyboardResponse } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const experiment = createExperiment({
  name: 'Simple Reaction Time',
  version: '1.0.0',
  description: 'Measure reaction time to visual stimulus'
})
.addTimeline(
  timeline => timeline
    .setName('main-timeline')
    .addStimulus(new TextStimulus('Press SPACE when you see this text'))
    .addResponse(new KeyboardResponse(['Space']))
    .setDuration(5000)
);

// Run the experiment
const results = await experiment.run();
console.log('Results:', results);
```

## API Reference

### Experiment Creation

#### createExperiment()

Create a new experiment with configuration:

```typescript
import { createExperiment } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const experiment = createExperiment({
  name: 'Stroop Color-Word Task',
  version: '1.0.0',
  description: 'Classic Stroop interference experiment',
  author: 'Research Team',
  institution: 'University Lab',
  metadata: {
    ethics: 'IRB-2024-001',
    funding: 'NSF Grant 12345'
  }
});
```

#### ExperimentConfig

```typescript
interface ExperimentConfig {
  name: string;
  version: string;
  description?: string;
  author?: string;
  institution?: string;
  metadata?: Record<string, any>;
  settings?: ExperimentSettings;
}
```

### Timeline Management

#### Timeline Creation

```typescript
const timeline = experiment.addTimeline(timeline => timeline
  .setName('practice-block')
  .setDescription('Practice trials with feedback')
  .setDuration(30000) // 30 seconds
  .setLoop(true)
  .setCondition(data => data.accuracy > 0.8)
);
```

#### Timeline Hierarchy

```typescript
// Main experiment timeline
const experiment = createExperiment({ name: 'Experiment' });

// Block-level timeline
const block = experiment.addTimeline(timeline => timeline
  .setName('block-1')
  .setDescription('First block of trials')
);

// Trial-level timeline
const trial = block.addChild(timeline => timeline
  .setName('trial-1')
  .setDescription('Individual trial')
  .addStimulus(new TextStimulus('Red'))
  .addResponse(new KeyboardResponse(['r', 'g', 'b']))
);
```

### Stimuli

#### TextStimulus

```typescript
import { TextStimulus } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const textStimulus = new TextStimulus('Hello World', {
  fontSize: 24,
  fontFamily: 'Arial',
  color: '#000000',
  backgroundColor: '#FFFFFF',
  position: { x: 50, y: 50 }, // Percentage of screen
  duration: 2000, // 2 seconds
  fadeIn: 250,
  fadeOut: 250
});
```

#### ImageStimulus

```typescript
import { ImageStimulus } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const imageStimulus = new ImageStimulus('/images/face.jpg', {
  width: 200,
  height: 200,
  position: { x: 50, y: 50 },
  duration: 1500,
  scaling: 'contain'
});
```

#### AudioStimulus

```typescript
import { AudioStimulus } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const audioStimulus = new AudioStimulus('/sounds/tone.wav', {
  volume: 0.7,
  loop: false,
  fadeIn: 100,
  fadeOut: 100,
  startTime: 0.5, // Start 500ms into the file
  duration: 2000
});
```

#### VideoStimulus

```typescript
import { VideoStimulus } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const videoStimulus = new VideoStimulus('/videos/instructions.mp4', {
  width: 800,
  height: 600,
  position: { x: 50, y: 50 },
  controls: false,
  autoplay: true,
  loop: false
});
```

### Response Collection

#### KeyboardResponse

```typescript
import { KeyboardResponse } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const keyboardResponse = new KeyboardResponse(['Space', 'Enter'], {
  timeout: 3000,
  allowedKeys: ['Space', 'Enter', 'Escape'],
  caseSensitive: false,
  continuous: false
});
```

#### MouseResponse

```typescript
import { MouseResponse } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const mouseResponse = new MouseResponse({
  buttons: ['left', 'right'],
  timeout: 5000,
  trackMovement: true,
  requireTarget: true,
  targetSelector: '.stimulus-container'
});
```

#### TouchResponse

```typescript
import { TouchResponse } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const touchResponse = new TouchResponse({
  maxTouches: 1,
  timeout: 4000,
  trackMovement: true,
  requireTarget: false,
  gestures: ['tap', 'swipe']
});
```

### Events

#### WaitEvent

```typescript
import { WaitEvent } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const waitEvent = new WaitEvent(1000); // Wait 1 second
timeline.addEvent(waitEvent);
```

#### ConditionalEvent

```typescript
import { ConditionalEvent } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const conditionalEvent = new ConditionalEvent({
  condition: (data) => data.accuracy > 0.8,
  trueAction: () => console.log('Good accuracy!'),
  falseAction: () => console.log('Need more practice')
});
```

#### LoopEvent

```typescript
import { LoopEvent } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

